## 4. Scalability Analysis & Partitioning Strategy

### 4.1 Table Volume Projections

| Table | Year 1 | Year 2 | Year 3 | Growth Pattern |
|-------|--------|--------|--------|----------------|
| `users` | 500K | 5M | 25M | Linear |
| `creator_profiles` | 10K | 100K | 500K | Linear |
| `posts` | 5M | 50M | 200M | Linear |
| `media` | 20M | 200M | 800M | Linear |
| `transactions` | 50M | 500M | 2B | Exponential |
| `messages` | 100M | 1B | 5B | Exponential |
| `notifications` | 500M | 5B | 20B | Exponential |
| `likes` | 50M | 500M | 2B | Exponential |
| `comments` (new) | 10M | 100M | 400M | Exponential |
| `post_analytics` | 50M | 500M | 2B | Linear (daily) |
| `creator_analytics` | 5M | 50M | 200M | Linear (daily) |
| `audit_logs` | 100M | 1B | 5B | Unbounded |
| `user_activity` (new) | 1B | 10B | 50B | Exponential |

### 4.2 Read/Write Pattern Analysis

| Table | Read Pattern | Write Pattern | Hot Path |
|-------|--------------|---------------|----------|
| `users` | Very High | Low | ✅ Auth, profiles |
| `posts` | Very High | Medium | ✅ Feed, discovery |
| `media` | Very High | Low | ✅ Content delivery |
| `subscriptions` | High | Medium | ✅ Access checks |
| `transactions` | Medium | High | Financial reporting |
| `messages` | High | High | ✅ Chat |
| `notifications` | High | Very High | ✅ Real-time |
| `likes` | Medium | High | Engagement |
| `post_analytics` | Low | Very High | Background jobs |
| `audit_logs` | Low | Very High | Compliance |

### 4.3 Partitioning Strategy (Human Decision: Best Practice)

**Tables to Partition FROM DAY ONE:**

| Table | Partition Strategy | Partition Key | Retention |
|-------|-------------------|---------------|-----------|
| `transactions` | Range by month | `created_at` | Indefinite |
| `messages` | Range by month | `created_at` | Indefinite |
| `notifications` | Range by month | `created_at` | 90 days active, archive older |
| `audit_logs` | Range by month | `created_at` | 2 years, then archive |
| `post_analytics` | Range by month | `date` | Indefinite |
| `creator_analytics` | Range by month | `date` | Indefinite |
| `user_activity` (new) | Range by week | `created_at` | 30 days hot, archive older |

**Partition Implementation Notes:**
- Use PostgreSQL native partitioning (PARTITION BY RANGE)
- Create partitions ahead of time (3 months in advance)
- Automate partition creation via cron job
- Consider pg_partman extension for automation

**Example Partition DDL:**
```sql
-- transactions table with partitioning
CREATE TABLE transactions (
  ...
) PARTITION BY RANGE (created_at);

-- Monthly partitions
CREATE TABLE transactions_2025_01 PARTITION OF transactions
  FOR VALUES FROM ('2025-01-01') TO ('2025-02-01');
```

### 4.4 Indexing Improvements

**Missing Composite Indexes (Add):**

| Table | Index | Purpose |
|-------|-------|---------|
| `posts` | `(creator_id, published_at DESC)` | Feed queries |
| `posts` | `(creator_id, status, published_at DESC)` | Creator dashboard |
| `messages` | `(conversation_id, is_read)` | Unread count |
| `messages` | `(conversation_id, created_at DESC)` | Message history |
| `subscriptions` | `(status, expires_at)` | Expiration jobs |
| `subscriptions` | `(creator_id, status)` | Subscriber lists |
| `notifications` | `(user_id, is_read, created_at DESC)` | Notification feed |
| `likes` | `(post_id, created_at DESC)` | Recent likes |
| `transactions` | `(creator_id, created_at DESC)` | Earnings history |

**Partial Indexes (Add for Performance):**

```sql
-- Only index active subscriptions for access checks
CREATE INDEX idx_subscriptions_active 
  ON subscriptions(user_id, creator_id) 
  WHERE status = 'active';

-- Only index unread notifications
CREATE INDEX idx_notifications_unread 
  ON notifications(user_id, created_at DESC) 
  WHERE is_read = FALSE;

-- Only index published posts for feed
CREATE INDEX idx_posts_published 
  ON posts(creator_id, published_at DESC) 
  WHERE status = 'published';
```

